<doc f='llvm/compiler-rt/lib/scudo/standalone/combined.h' l='740'>// Return the usable size for a given chunk. Technically we lie, as we just
  // report the actual size of a chunk. This is done to counteract code actively
  // writing past the end of a chunk (like sqlite3) when the usable size allows
  // for it, which then forces realloc to copy the usable size of a chunk as
  // opposed to its actual size.</doc>
<use f='llvm/compiler-rt/lib/scudo/standalone/wrappers_c.inc' l='67' u='c' c='malloc_usable_size'/>
